    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="72"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d72">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoyt</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of Justice</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 4, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    letter of April 2, requesting copy of my report on the trial of Sheriff Martin
                    and his deputies, and I beg to say in reply that I shall place the report in
                    your hands during the current week, and as early in the week as possible. Other
                    matters seem to have required my more immediate attention here, and for this
                    reason the report has been somewhat delayed. I regret extremely if this delay
                    has caused you any embarrassment whatever.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry M. Hoyt</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Assistant Attorney-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
